11#ifndef MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_SENDER_EGRESS_H_
12#define MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_SENDER_EGRESS_H_

14#include <map>
15#include <memory>
16#include <utility>
17#include <vector>
18
19#include "absl/types/optional.h"
20#include "api/call/transport.h"
21#include "api/rtc_event_log/rtc_event_log.h"

31#include "rtc_base/rate_statistics.h"
32#include "rtc_base/synchronization/mutex.h"
33#include "rtc_base/system/no_unique_address.h"
34#include "rtc_base/task_utils/pending_task_safety_flag.h"
35#include "rtc_base/task_utils/repeating_task.h"

38namespace webrtc {
39
40class RtpSenderEgress {
41 public:
42 // Helper class that redirects packets directly to the send part of this class
43 // without passing through an actual paced sender.
44 class NonPacedPacketSender : public RtpPacketSender {
45 public:
46 NonPacedPacketSender(RtpSenderEgress* sender,
47 SequenceNumberAssigner* sequence_number_assigner);
48 virtual ~NonPacedPacketSender();
49
50 void EnqueuePackets(
51 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets) override;
52
53 private:
54 void PrepareForSend(RtpPacketToSend* packet);
55 uint16_t transport_sequence_number_;
56 RtpSenderEgress* const sender_;
57 SequenceNumberAssigner* sequence_number_assigner_;
58 };
59
60 RtpSenderEgress(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config,
61 RtpPacketHistory* packet_history);
62 ~RtpSenderEgress();
63
64 void SendPacket(RtpPacketToSend* packet, const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info)
65 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
66 uint32_t Ssrc() const { return ssrc_; }
67 absl::optional<uint32_t> RtxSsrc() const { return rtx_ssrc_; }
68 absl::optional<uint32_t> FlexFecSsrc() const { return flexfec_ssrc_; }
69
70 RtpSendRates GetSendRates() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
71 void GetDataCounters(StreamDataCounters* rtp_stats,
72 StreamDataCounters* rtx_stats) const
73 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
74
75 void ForceIncludeSendPacketsInAllocation(bool part_of_allocation)
76 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
77 bool MediaHasBeenSent() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
78 void SetMediaHasBeenSent(bool media_sent) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
79 void SetTimestampOffset(uint32_t timestamp) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
80
81 // For each sequence number in |sequence_number|, recall the last RTP packet
82 // which bore it - its timestamp and whether it was the first and/or last
83 // packet in that frame. If all of the given sequence numbers could be
84 // recalled, return a vector with all of them (in corresponding order).
85 // If any could not be recalled, return an empty vector.
86 std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info> GetSentRtpPacketInfos(
87 rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> sequence_numbers) const
88 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(lock_);
89
90 void SetFecProtectionParameters(const FecProtectionParams& delta_params,
91 const FecProtectionParams& key_params);
92 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> FetchFecPackets();
93
94 private:
95 // Maps capture time in milliseconds to send-side delay in milliseconds.
96 // Send-side delay is the difference between transmission time and capture
97 // time.
98 typedef std::map<int64_t, int> SendDelayMap;
99
100 RtpSendRates GetSendRatesLocked(int64_t now_ms) const
101 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
102 bool HasCorrectSsrc(const RtpPacketToSend& packet) const;
103 void AddPacketToTransportFeedback(uint16_t packet_id,
104 const RtpPacketToSend& packet,
105 const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info);
106 void UpdateDelayStatistics(int64_t capture_time_ms,
107 int64_t now_ms,
108 uint32_t ssrc);
109 void RecomputeMaxSendDelay() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
110 void UpdateOnSendPacket(int packet_id,
111 int64_t capture_time_ms,
112 uint32_t ssrc);
113 // Sends packet on to |transport_|, leaving the RTP module.
114 bool SendPacketToNetwork(const RtpPacketToSend& packet,
115 const PacketOptions& options,
116 const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info);
117
118 void UpdateRtpStats(int64_t now_ms,
119 uint32_t packet_ssrc,
120 RtpPacketMediaType packet_type,
121 RtpPacketCounter counter,
122 size_t packet_size);
123#if BWE_TEST_LOGGING_COMPILE_TIME_ENABLE
124 void BweTestLoggingPlot(int64_t now_ms, uint32_t packet_ssrc);
125#endif
126
127 // Called on a timer, once a second, on the worker_queue_.
128 void PeriodicUpdate();
129
130 TaskQueueBase* const worker_queue_;
131 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker pacer_checker_;
132 const uint32_t ssrc_;
133 const absl::optional<uint32_t> rtx_ssrc_;
134 const absl::optional<uint32_t> flexfec_ssrc_;
135 const bool populate_network2_timestamp_;
136 const bool send_side_bwe_with_overhead_;
137 Clock* const clock_;
138 RtpPacketHistory* const packet_history_;
139 Transport* const transport_;
140 RtcEventLog* const event_log_;
141#if BWE_TEST_LOGGING_COMPILE_TIME_ENABLE
142 const bool is_audio_;
143#endif
144 const bool need_rtp_packet_infos_;
145 VideoFecGenerator* const fec_generator_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(pacer_checker_);
146
147 TransportFeedbackObserver* const transport_feedback_observer_;
148 SendSideDelayObserver* const send_side_delay_observer_;
149 SendPacketObserver* const send_packet_observer_;
150 StreamDataCountersCallback* const rtp_stats_callback_;
151 BitrateStatisticsObserver* const bitrate_callback_;
152
153 mutable Mutex lock_;
154 bool media_has_been_sent_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(pacer_checker_);
155 bool force_part_of_allocation_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
156 uint32_t timestamp_offset_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_queue_);
157
158 SendDelayMap send_delays_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
159 SendDelayMap::const_iterator max_delay_it_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
160 // The sum of delays over a kSendSideDelayWindowMs sliding window.
161 int64_t sum_delays_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
162 uint64_t total_packet_send_delay_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
163 StreamDataCounters rtp_stats_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
164 StreamDataCounters rtx_rtp_stats_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
165 // One element per value in RtpPacketMediaType, with index matching value.
166 std::vector<RateStatistics> send_rates_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
167 absl::optional<std::pair<FecProtectionParams, FecProtectionParams>>
168 pending_fec_params_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
169
170 // Maps sent packets' sequence numbers to a tuple consisting of:
171 // 1. The timestamp, without the randomizing offset mandated by the RFC.
172 // 2. Whether the packet was the first in its frame.
173 // 3. Whether the packet was the last in its frame.
174 const std::unique_ptr<RtpSequenceNumberMap> rtp_sequence_number_map_
175 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_queue_);
176 RepeatingTaskHandle update_task_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_queue_);
177 ScopedTaskSafety task_safety_;
178};
179
180} // namespace webrtc
181
182#endif // MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_SENDER_EGRESS_H_
